64	\section{\'Etale sheafification}
65	
66	The \'etale-sheafified relative Picard functor is built on top of $\PicardFunctorAb$. The Mathlib gap that previously blocked this (sheafification for the \'etale topology over $\Spec k$ valued in $\AddCommGrpCat$) closed in current Mathlib. Post-iter-109 (cascading from the C1 promotion of $\mathrm{LineBundle}$ in Chapter~\ref{chap:Picard_LineBundle}), the codomain of $\PicardFunctorAb$ has bumped from $\AddCommGrpCat.\{u\}$ to $\AddCommGrpCat.\{u+1\}$: the C1 refactor pushed $\Pic\,X$ into $\mathrm{Type}\,(u+1)$, $\PicardFunctor$ inherited the bump (landing in $\mathrm{Type}\,(u+1)$ rather than $\mathrm{Type}\,u$), and $\PicardFunctorAb$ in turn followed (landing in $\AddCommGrpCat.\{u+1\}$ rather than $\AddCommGrpCat.\{u\}$). The post-iter-109 codomain $\AddCommGrpCat.\{u+1\}$ already matches the value-universe at which Mathlib's $\mathrm{HasSheafify}$ instance for the \'etale topology over $\Spec k$ is inferable, so the universe-pinning gymnastic that the pre-iter-109 framing required (post-composing with the natural universe lift $\AddCommGrpCat.\{u\} \to \AddCommGrpCat.\{u+1\}$) is no longer needed: the body of $\mathrm{etaleSheafified}$ simplifies by one functor composition.
67	
68	\begin{definition}\leanok
69	[\'Etale-sheafified relative Picard functor]
70	  \label{def:PicardFunctorAb_etaleSheafified}
71	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.PicardFunctorAb.etaleSheafified}
72	  \uses{def:Pic_functorAb}
73	  Let $C$ be a scheme over $\Spec k$. The \emph{\'etale-sheafified relative Picard functor} of $C$ over $k$ is the \'etale sheaf on $\Sch_k$ obtained by sheafifying $\PicardFunctorAb\, C$ directly. Post-iter-109 (cascading from the C1 promotion of Chapter~\ref{chap:Picard_LineBundle}), $\PicardFunctorAb\, C$ already lands in $\AddCommGrpCat.\{u+1\}$ --- the value-universe at which the \'etale-topology sheafification over $\Spec k$ is inferable in current Mathlib --- so the pre-iter-109 universe-lift composition $\AddCommGrpCat.\{u\} \to \AddCommGrpCat.\{u+1\}$ that bridged the iter-004 codomain $\AddCommGrpCat.\{u\}$ to that value-universe is no longer needed.
74	\end{definition}
75	
76	\begin{proof}
77	  \uses{def:Pic_functorAb}
78	  \leanok
79	  Apply the Mathlib sheafification left-adjoint to $\PicardFunctorAb\, C$ directly. The two sheafification instances are inferable in current Mathlib for the \'etale topology over $\Spec k$ valued in $\AddCommGrpCat.\{u+1\}$, so sheafification types out without extra hypotheses on the (post-iter-109) codomain $\AddCommGrpCat.\{u+1\}$ of $\PicardFunctorAb$ --- no universe-lift composition is interposed.
80	\end{proof}
